Note: Runa Standard Library - Zero-Knowledge Proof Systems
This module provides production-grade zero-knowledge proof systems including
zk-SNARKs, zk-STARKs, Bulletproofs, and interactive proof protocols.

Supports circuit-based proofs, range proofs, membership proofs, and advanced
cryptographic protocols for privacy-preserving computation and verification.

Specification compliance: Groth16, PLONK, FRI-based STARKs, Bulletproofs protocol.
:End Note

Import "crypto/primitives/curve" as curve
Import "crypto/primitives/field" as field
Import "crypto/primitives/bignum" as bignum
Import "crypto/primitives/random" as random
Import "crypto/hash" as hash

Type ZkpResult is Union with:
    ZkpSuccess with value as Dictionary[String, Any]
    ZkpFailure with error as ZkpError and message as String

Type ZkpError is Enum with:
    Invalid_Circuit
    Invalid_Witness
    Invalid_Proof
    Verification_Failed
    Setup_Failed
    Constraint_Violation
    Parameter_Generation_Failed
    Serialization_Failed
    Unsupported_Operation
    Internal_Error

Type ZkProofSystem is Enum with:
    Groth16
    PLONK
    Bulletproofs
    zk_STARK
    zk_SNARK_Generic
    Sigma_Protocol

Type called "ZkCircuit":
    gates as List[ZkGate]
    public_inputs as List[Integer]
    private_inputs as List[Integer]
    constraints as List[ZkConstraint]
    circuit_size as Integer
    depth as Integer

Type called "ZkGate":
    gate_type as ZkGateType
    inputs as List[Integer]
    output as Integer
    coefficient as Optional[field.FieldElement]

Type ZkGateType is Enum with:
    ADD
    MUL
    CONSTANT
    PUBLIC_INPUT
    PRIVATE_INPUT

Type called "ZkConstraint":
    constraint_type as ZkConstraintType
    variables as List[Integer]
    coefficients as List[field.FieldElement]
    constant as field.FieldElement

Type ZkConstraintType is Enum with:
    Linear_Combination
    Quadratic_Constraint
    Range_Constraint
    Boolean_Constraint

Type called "ZkWitness":
    private_values as List[field.FieldElement]
    public_values as List[field.FieldElement]
    intermediate_values as List[field.FieldElement]
    assignment_valid as Boolean

Type called "ZkProof":
    proof_system as ZkProofSystem
    proof_data as List[Integer]
    public_inputs as List[field.FieldElement]
    verification_key_hash as List[Integer]
    proof_size as Integer
    generation_time_ms as Integer

Type called "ZkVerificationKey":
    proof_system as ZkProofSystem
    key_data as List[Integer]
    circuit_hash as List[Integer]
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    key_size as Integer

Type called "ZkProvingKey":
    proof_system as ZkProofSystem
    key_data as List[Integer]
    circuit_hash as List[Integer]
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    key_size as Integer

Type called "ZkSetupParameters":
    proof_system as ZkProofSystem
    security_level as Integer
    circuit_size as Integer
    random_oracle as String
    curve_parameters as curve.EllipticCurve
    field_parameters as field.PrimeField

Type called "BulletproofRange":
    value as bignum.BigInteger
    min_value as bignum.BigInteger
    max_value as bignum.BigInteger
    bit_length as Integer

Type called "SigmaProtocolStatement":
    protocol_type as String
    public_parameters as List[curve.EllipticCurvePoint]
    statement as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "SigmaProtocolWitness":
    secret_values as List[bignum.BigInteger]
    randomness as List[bignum.BigInteger]

Note: ZKP System Constants
Let DEFAULT_SECURITY_LEVEL be 128
Let GROTH16_PROOF_SIZE be 192  Note: 3 group elements * 64 bytes
Let PLONK_PROOF_SIZE be 256
let BULLETPROOF_BASE_SIZE be 64
Let MAX_CIRCUIT_SIZE be 1048576  Note: 2^20 gates
Let FIAT_SHAMIR_DOMAIN_SEPARATOR be "runa_zkp_fiat_shamir_v1"

Note: Primary Zero-Knowledge Proof Interface

Process called "setup_zkp_system" that takes proof_system as ZkProofSystem and circuit as ZkCircuit and security_level as Integer returns ZkpResult[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Setup zero-knowledge proof system with circuit and security parameters
    Try:
        Note: Validate circuit
        Let circuit_validation_result be validate_circuit with circuit as circuit
        Match circuit_validation_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return circuit_validation_result
            When ZkpSuccess:
                Note: Check circuit size limits
                If circuit.circuit_size is greater than MAX_CIRCUIT_SIZE:
                    Return ZkpFailure with:
                        error as ZkpError.Invalid_Circuit
                        message as "Circuit size exceeds maximum supported size"
                
                Note: Generate setup parameters
                Let setup_params_result be generate_setup_parameters with proof_system as proof_system and circuit as circuit and security_level as security_level
                Match setup_params_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return setup_params_result
                    When ZkpSuccess with value as setup_params:
                        Note: Perform system-specific setup
                        Match proof_system:
                            When ZkProofSystem.Groth16:
                                Return setup_groth16 with circuit as circuit and params as setup_params
                            When ZkProofSystem.PLONK:
                                Return setup_plonk with circuit as circuit and params as setup_params
                            When ZkProofSystem.Bulletproofs:
                                Return setup_bulletproofs with circuit as circuit and params as setup_params
                            When ZkProofSystem.zk_STARK:
                                Return setup_zk_stark with circuit as circuit and params as setup_params
                            When ZkProofSystem.Sigma_Protocol:
                                Return setup_sigma_protocol with circuit as circuit and params as setup_params
                            Otherwise:
                                Return ZkpFailure with:
                                    error as ZkpError.Unsupported_Operation
                                    message as "Proof system not yet implemented: " plus (proof_system as String)
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Setup_Failed
            message as "ZKP system setup error: " plus error as String

Process called "generate_zkp_proof" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and witness as ZkWitness and proving_key as ZkProvingKey returns ZkpResult[ZkProof]:
    Note: Generate zero-knowledge proof for circuit with witness
    Try:
        Let start_time be time.now
        
        Note: Validate witness against circuit
        Let witness_validation_result be validate_witness with circuit as circuit and witness as witness
        Match witness_validation_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return witness_validation_result
            When ZkpSuccess:
                Note: Check that witness satisfies all constraints
                Let constraint_check_result be check_circuit_constraints with circuit as circuit and witness as witness
                Match constraint_check_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return constraint_check_result
                    When ZkpSuccess:
                        Note: Generate proof based on system type
                        Let proof_result be None
                        Match proving_key.proof_system:
                            When ZkProofSystem.Groth16:
                                Set proof_result to generate_groth16_proof with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and proving_key as proving_key
                            When ZkProofSystem.PLONK:
                                Set proof_result to generate_plonk_proof with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and proving_key as proving_key
                            When ZkProofSystem.Bulletproofs:
                                Set proof_result to generate_bulletproof with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and proving_key as proving_key
                            When ZkProofSystem.zk_STARK:
                                Set proof_result to generate_zk_stark_proof with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and proving_key as proving_key
                            When ZkProofSystem.Sigma_Protocol:
                                Set proof_result to generate_sigma_protocol_proof with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and proving_key as proving_key
                            Otherwise:
                                Return ZkpFailure with:
                                    error as ZkpError.Unsupported_Operation
                                    message as "Proof generation not implemented for system: " plus (proving_key.proof_system as String)
                        
                        Match proof_result:
                            When ZkpFailure:
                                Return proof_result
                            When ZkpSuccess with value as proof_data:
                                Let end_time be time.now
                                Let generation_time be time.difference_milliseconds with start_time as start_time and end_time as end_time
                                
                                Let zkp_proof be ZkProof with:
                                    proof_system as proving_key.proof_system
                                    proof_data as proof_data
                                    public_inputs as witness.public_values
                                    verification_key_hash as hash_verification_key with proving_key as proving_key
                                    proof_size as (length of proof_data)
                                    generation_time_ms as generation_time
                                
                                Return ZkpSuccess with value as zkp_proof
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Internal_Error
            message as "ZKP proof generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "verify_zkp_proof" that takes proof as ZkProof and verification_key as ZkVerificationKey and public_inputs as List[field.FieldElement] returns ZkpResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Verify zero-knowledge proof
    Try:
        Note: Validate proof system compatibility
        If proof.proof_system is not equal to verification_key.proof_system:
            Return ZkpFailure with:
                error as ZkpError.Invalid_Proof
                message as "Proof system mismatch between proof and verification key"
        
        Note: Validate public inputs
        If (length of public_inputs) is not equal to (length of proof.public_inputs):
            Return ZkpFailure with:
                error as ZkpError.Invalid_Proof
                message as "Public input count mismatch"
        
        For i from 0 to (length of public_inputs minus 1):
            If not field_elements_equal with a as (public_inputs at index i) and b as (proof.public_inputs at index i):
                Return ZkpFailure with:
                    error as ZkpError.Invalid_Proof
                    message as "Public input value mismatch at index " plus (i as String)
        
        Note: Perform system-specific verification
        Let verification_result be None
        Match proof.proof_system:
            When ZkProofSystem.Groth16:
                Set verification_result to verify_groth16_proof with proof as proof and verification_key as verification_key and public_inputs as public_inputs
            When ZkProofSystem.PLONK:
                Set verification_result to verify_plonk_proof with proof as proof and verification_key as verification_key and public_inputs as public_inputs
            When ZkProofSystem.Bulletproofs:
                Set verification_result to verify_bulletproof with proof as proof and verification_key as verification_key and public_inputs as public_inputs
            When ZkProofSystem.zk_STARK:
                Set verification_result to verify_zk_stark_proof with proof as proof and verification_key as verification_key and public_inputs as public_inputs
            When ZkProofSystem.Sigma_Protocol:
                Set verification_result to verify_sigma_protocol_proof with proof as proof and verification_key as verification_key and public_inputs as public_inputs
            Otherwise:
                Return ZkpFailure with:
                    error as ZkpError.Unsupported_Operation
                    message as "Proof verification not implemented for system: " plus (proof.proof_system as String)
        
        Return verification_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Verification_Failed
            message as "ZKP proof verification error: " plus error as String

Note: Groth16 Implementation

Process called "setup_groth16" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and params as ZkSetupParameters returns ZkpResult[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Setup Groth16 zk-SNARK system
    Try:
        Note: Generate toxic waste (structured reference string)
        Let toxic_waste_result be generate_groth16_toxic_waste with circuit as circuit and params as params
        Match toxic_waste_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return toxic_waste_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as toxic_waste:
                Note: Generate proving key
                Let proving_key_result be generate_groth16_proving_key with circuit as circuit and toxic_waste as toxic_waste and params as params
                Match proving_key_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return proving_key_result
                    When ZkpSuccess with value as proving_key:
                        Note: Generate verification key
                        Let verification_key_result be generate_groth16_verification_key with circuit as circuit and toxic_waste as toxic_waste and params as params
                        Match verification_key_result:
                            When ZkpFailure:
                                Return verification_key_result
                            When ZkpSuccess with value as verification_key:
                                Note: Securely delete toxic waste
                                Clear_toxic_waste with toxic_waste as toxic_waste
                                
                                Let setup_result be dictionary containing:
                                    "proving_key" as proving_key,
                                    "verification_key" as verification_key,
                                    "circuit_hash" as hash_circuit with circuit as circuit
                                
                                Return ZkpSuccess with value as setup_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Setup_Failed
            message as "Groth16 setup error: " plus error as String

Process called "generate_groth16_proof" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and witness as ZkWitness and proving_key as ZkProvingKey returns ZkpResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Generate Groth16 proof
    Try:
        Note: Sample random values for proof generation
        Let r_result be random.generate_random_field_element with field as proving_key.parameters["field"]
        Let s_result be random.generate_random_field_element with field as proving_key.parameters["field"]
        
        Match r_result:
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return ZkpFailure with:
                    error as ZkpError.Parameter_Generation_Failed
                    message as "Failed to generate random r for Groth16"
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as r:
                Match s_result:
                    When random.RandomFailure:
                        Return ZkpFailure with:
                            error as ZkpError.Parameter_Generation_Failed
                            message as "Failed to generate random s for Groth16"
                    When random.RandomSuccess with value as s:
                        Note: Compute proof elements A, B, C
                        Let proof_a_result be compute_groth16_proof_a with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and r as r and proving_key as proving_key
                        Match proof_a_result:
                            When ZkpFailure:
                                Return proof_a_result
                            When ZkpSuccess with value as proof_a:
                                Let proof_b_result be compute_groth16_proof_b with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and s as s and proving_key as proving_key
                                Match proof_b_result:
                                    When ZkpFailure:
                                        Return proof_b_result
                                    When ZkpSuccess with value as proof_b:
                                        Let proof_c_result be compute_groth16_proof_c with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and r as r and s as s and proof_a as proof_a and proof_b as proof_b and proving_key as proving_key
                                        Match proof_c_result:
                                            When ZkpFailure:
                                                Return proof_c_result
                                            When ZkpSuccess with value as proof_c:
                                                Note: Serialize proof elements
                                                Let proof_serialized be serialize_groth16_proof with a as proof_a and b as proof_b and c as proof_c
                                                Return ZkpSuccess with value as proof_serialized
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Internal_Error
            message as "Groth16 proof generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "verify_groth16_proof" that takes proof as ZkProof and verification_key as ZkVerificationKey and public_inputs as List[field.FieldElement] returns ZkpResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Verify Groth16 proof using pairing operations
    Try:
        Note: Deserialize proof elements
        Let proof_elements_result be deserialize_groth16_proof with proof_data as proof.proof_data
        Match proof_elements_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return proof_elements_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as proof_elements:
                Let proof_a be proof_elements["A"]
                Let proof_b be proof_elements["B"]
                Let proof_c be proof_elements["C"]
                
                Note: Compute public input linear combination
                Let public_input_lc_result be compute_public_input_linear_combination with public_inputs as public_inputs and verification_key as verification_key
                Match public_input_lc_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return public_input_lc_result
                    When ZkpSuccess with value as public_input_lc:
                        Note: Perform pairing check: e(A,B) = e(alpha, beta) * e(public_input_lc + C, gamma) * e(C, delta)
                        Let pairing_result be groth16_pairing_check with proof_a as proof_a and proof_b as proof_b and proof_c as proof_c and public_input_lc as public_input_lc and verification_key as verification_key
                        Match pairing_result:
                            When ZkpSuccess with value as pairing_valid:
                                Return ZkpSuccess with value as pairing_valid
                            When ZkpFailure:
                                Return ZkpFailure with:
                                    error as ZkpError.Verification_Failed
                                    message as "Groth16 pairing check failed"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Verification_Failed
            message as "Groth16 verification error: " plus error as String

Note: Bulletproofs Implementation

Process called "setup_bulletproofs" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and params as ZkSetupParameters returns ZkpResult[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Setup Bulletproofs system (transparent setup)
    Try:
        Note: Generate random generators for Pedersen commitments
        Let generators_result be generate_bulletproof_generators with count as circuit.circuit_size and params as params
        Match generators_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return generators_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as generators:
                Note: Create proving key (generators and circuit)
                Let proving_key be ZkProvingKey with:
                    proof_system as ZkProofSystem.Bulletproofs
                    key_data as serialize_bulletproof_generators with generators as generators
                    circuit_hash as hash_circuit with circuit as circuit
                    parameters as dictionary containing: "generators" as generators, "field" as params.field_parameters
                    key_size as (length of serialize_bulletproof_generators with generators as generators)
                
                Note: Create verification key (same as proving key for Bulletproofs)
                Let verification_key be ZkVerificationKey with:
                    proof_system as ZkProofSystem.Bulletproofs
                    key_data as serialize_bulletproof_generators with generators as generators
                    circuit_hash as hash_circuit with circuit as circuit
                    parameters as dictionary containing: "generators" as generators, "field" as params.field_parameters
                    key_size as (length of serialize_bulletproof_generators with generators as generators)
                
                Let setup_result be dictionary containing:
                    "proving_key" as proving_key,
                    "verification_key" as verification_key,
                    "circuit_hash" as hash_circuit with circuit as circuit
                
                Return ZkpSuccess with value as setup_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Setup_Failed
            message as "Bulletproofs setup error: " plus error as String

Process called "generate_bulletproof" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and witness as ZkWitness and proving_key as ZkProvingKey returns ZkpResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Generate Bulletproof for circuit satisfaction
    Try:
        Note: Create Pedersen commitments for witness values
        Let commitments_result be create_pedersen_commitments with values as witness.private_values and generators as proving_key.parameters["generators"]
        Match commitments_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return commitments_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as commitments:
                Note: Generate inner product argument
                Let inner_product_result be generate_inner_product_argument with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and commitments as commitments and proving_key as proving_key
                Match inner_product_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return inner_product_result
                    When ZkpSuccess with value as inner_product_proof:
                        Note: Combine commitments and inner product proof
                        Let bulletproof_data be serialize_bulletproof with commitments as commitments and inner_product_proof as inner_product_proof
                        Return ZkpSuccess with value as bulletproof_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Internal_Error
            message as "Bulletproof generation error: " plus error as String

Note: Range Proof Functionality

Process called "generate_range_proof" that takes value as bignum.BigInteger and min_value as bignum.BigInteger and max_value as bignum.BigInteger and bit_length as Integer returns ZkpResult[ZkProof]:
    Note: Generate zero-knowledge range proof
    Try:
        Note: Validate range parameters
        If bignum.compare with a as value and b as min_value is equal to -1 or bignum.compare with a as value and b as max_value is equal to 1:
            Return ZkpFailure with:
                error as ZkpError.Invalid_Witness
                message as "Value is outside specified range"
        
        Note: Create range circuit
        Let range_circuit_result be create_range_circuit with bit_length as bit_length
        Match range_circuit_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return range_circuit_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as range_circuit:
                Note: Create witness for value
                Let range_witness_result be create_range_witness with value as value and bit_length as bit_length
                Match range_witness_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return range_witness_result
                    When ZkpSuccess with value as range_witness:
                        Note: Setup Bulletproofs for range proof
                        Let setup_result be setup_bulletproofs with circuit as range_circuit and params as create_default_setup_parameters()
                        Match setup_result:
                            When ZkpFailure:
                                Return setup_result
                            When ZkpSuccess with value as setup_data:
                                Note: Generate proof
                                Let proof_result be generate_zkp_proof with circuit as range_circuit and witness as range_witness and proving_key as setup_data["proving_key"]
                                Return proof_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Internal_Error
            message as "Range proof generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "verify_range_proof" that takes proof as ZkProof and min_value as bignum.BigInteger and max_value as bignum.BigInteger and bit_length as Integer returns ZkpResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Verify zero-knowledge range proof
    Try:
        Note: Recreate range circuit for verification
        Let range_circuit_result be create_range_circuit with bit_length as bit_length
        Match range_circuit_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return range_circuit_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as range_circuit:
                Note: Extract verification key from proof metadata
                Let verification_key_result be extract_verification_key_from_proof with proof as proof
                Match verification_key_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return verification_key_result
                    When ZkpSuccess with value as verification_key:
                        Note: Verify proof
                        Let verification_result be verify_zkp_proof with proof as proof and verification_key as verification_key and public_inputs as empty list
                        Return verification_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Verification_Failed
            message as "Range proof verification error: " plus error as String

Note: Sigma Protocol Implementation

Process called "setup_sigma_protocol" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and params as ZkSetupParameters returns ZkpResult[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Setup Sigma protocol for interactive/non-interactive proofs
    Try:
        Note: Generate system parameters (generators)
        Let generators_result be generate_sigma_protocol_generators with params as params
        Match generators_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return generators_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as generators:
                Let proving_key be ZkProvingKey with:
                    proof_system as ZkProofSystem.Sigma_Protocol
                    key_data as serialize_sigma_generators with generators as generators
                    circuit_hash as hash_circuit with circuit as circuit
                    parameters as dictionary containing: "generators" as generators, "curve" as params.curve_parameters
                    key_size as (length of serialize_sigma_generators with generators as generators)
                
                Let verification_key be ZkVerificationKey with:
                    proof_system as ZkProofSystem.Sigma_Protocol
                    key_data as serialize_sigma_generators with generators as generators
                    circuit_hash as hash_circuit with circuit as circuit
                    parameters as dictionary containing: "generators" as generators, "curve" as params.curve_parameters
                    key_size as (length of serialize_sigma_generators with generators as generators)
                
                Let setup_result be dictionary containing:
                    "proving_key" as proving_key,
                    "verification_key" as verification_key,
                    "generators" as generators
                
                Return ZkpSuccess with value as setup_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Setup_Failed
            message as "Sigma protocol setup error: " plus error as String

Process called "generate_sigma_protocol_proof" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and witness as ZkWitness and proving_key as ZkProvingKey returns ZkpResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Generate non-interactive Sigma protocol proof using Fiat-Shamir transform
    Try:
        Note: Commitment phase - generate random values and commitments
        Let commitment_result be sigma_protocol_commit with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and proving_key as proving_key
        Match commitment_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return commitment_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as commitment_data:
                Note: Challenge phase - use Fiat-Shamir transform to generate challenge
                Let challenge_result be fiat_shamir_challenge with commitment as commitment_data["commitment"] and public_inputs as witness.public_values
                Match challenge_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return challenge_result
                    When ZkpSuccess with value as challenge:
                        Note: Response phase - generate response using witness and challenge
                        Let response_result be sigma_protocol_respond with circuit as circuit and witness as witness and commitment_data as commitment_data and challenge as challenge and proving_key as proving_key
                        Match response_result:
                            When ZkpFailure:
                                Return response_result
                            When ZkpSuccess with value as response:
                                Note: Serialize proof (commitment, challenge, response)
                                Let proof_serialized be serialize_sigma_proof with commitment as commitment_data["commitment"] and challenge as challenge and response as response
                                Return ZkpSuccess with value as proof_serialized
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Internal_Error
            message as "Sigma protocol proof generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "verify_sigma_protocol_proof" that takes proof as ZkProof and verification_key as ZkVerificationKey and public_inputs as List[field.FieldElement] returns ZkpResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Verify non-interactive Sigma protocol proof
    Try:
        Note: Deserialize proof components
        Let proof_components_result be deserialize_sigma_proof with proof_data as proof.proof_data
        Match proof_components_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return proof_components_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as components:
                Let commitment be components["commitment"]
                Let challenge be components["challenge"]
                Let response be components["response"]
                
                Note: Recompute challenge using Fiat-Shamir transform
                Let recomputed_challenge_result be fiat_shamir_challenge with commitment as commitment and public_inputs as public_inputs
                Match recomputed_challenge_result:
                    When ZkpFailure:
                        Return recomputed_challenge_result
                    When ZkpSuccess with value as recomputed_challenge:
                        Note: Check challenge consistency
                        If not field_elements_equal with a as challenge and b as recomputed_challenge:
                            Return ZkpSuccess with value as false
                        
                        Note: Verify the Sigma protocol relation
                        Let verification_result be verify_sigma_relation with commitment as commitment and challenge as challenge and response as response and public_inputs as public_inputs and verification_key as verification_key
                        Return verification_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Verification_Failed
            message as "Sigma protocol verification error: " plus error as String

Note: Circuit and Constraint Validation

Process called "validate_circuit" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit returns ZkpResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Validate circuit structure and constraints
    Try:
        Note: Check basic circuit properties
        If (length of circuit.gates) is equal to 0:
            Return ZkpFailure with:
                error as ZkpError.Invalid_Circuit
                message as "Circuit must have at least one gate"
        
        If circuit.circuit_size is not equal to (length of circuit.gates):
            Return ZkpFailure with:
                error as ZkpError.Invalid_Circuit
                message as "Circuit size mismatch with gate count"
        
        Note: Validate each gate
        For i from 0 to (length of circuit.gates minus 1):
            Let gate be circuit.gates at index i
            Let gate_validation_result be validate_gate with gate as gate and circuit_size as circuit.circuit_size
            Match gate_validation_result:
                When ZkpFailure:
                    Return gate_validation_result
                When ZkpSuccess:
                    Note: Continue validation
        
        Note: Validate constraints
        For constraint in circuit.constraints:
            Let constraint_validation_result be validate_constraint with constraint as constraint and circuit_size as circuit.circuit_size
            Match constraint_validation_result:
                When ZkpFailure:
                    Return constraint_validation_result
                When ZkpSuccess:
                    Note: Continue validation
        
        Return ZkpSuccess with value as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Invalid_Circuit
            message as "Circuit validation error: " plus error as String

Process called "validate_witness" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and witness as ZkWitness returns ZkpResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Validate witness against circuit requirements
    Try:
        Note: Check witness structure
        If (length of witness.public_values) is not equal to (length of circuit.public_inputs):
            Return ZkpFailure with:
                error as ZkpError.Invalid_Witness
                message as "Public input count mismatch between witness and circuit"
        
        If (length of witness.private_values) is not equal to (length of circuit.private_inputs):
            Return ZkpFailure with:
                error as ZkpError.Invalid_Witness
                message as "Private input count mismatch between witness and circuit"
        
        Note: Validate witness values are in valid field
        For public_value in witness.public_values:
            If not field.is_valid_element with element as public_value:
                Return ZkpFailure with:
                    error as ZkpError.Invalid_Witness
                    message as "Invalid public witness value (not in field)"
        
        For private_value in witness.private_values:
            If not field.is_valid_element with element as private_value:
                Return ZkpFailure with:
                    error as ZkpError.Invalid_Witness
                    message as "Invalid private witness value (not in field)"
        
        Return ZkpSuccess with value as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Invalid_Witness
            message as "Witness validation error: " plus error as String

Process called "check_circuit_constraints" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit and witness as ZkWitness returns ZkpResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Check that witness satisfies all circuit constraints
    Try:
        Note: Evaluate all gates with witness values
        Let gate_values_result be evaluate_circuit_gates with circuit as circuit and witness as witness
        Match gate_values_result:
            When ZkpFailure:
                Return gate_values_result
            When ZkpSuccess with value as gate_values:
                Note: Check each constraint
                For constraint in circuit.constraints:
                    Let constraint_satisfied_result be evaluate_constraint with constraint as constraint and gate_values as gate_values and witness as witness
                    Match constraint_satisfied_result:
                        When ZkpFailure:
                            Return constraint_satisfied_result
                        When ZkpSuccess with value as satisfied:
                            If not satisfied:
                                Return ZkpFailure with:
                                    error as ZkpError.Constraint_Violation
                                    message as "Constraint not satisfied by witness"
                
                Return ZkpSuccess with value as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Constraint_Violation
            message as "Constraint checking error: " plus error as String

Note: Fiat-Shamir Transform

Process called "fiat_shamir_challenge" that takes commitment as List[Integer] and public_inputs as List[field.FieldElement] returns ZkpResult[field.FieldElement]:
    Note: Generate challenge using Fiat-Shamir transform
    Try:
        Note: Serialize commitment and public inputs
        Let challenge_input be serialize_fiat_shamir_input with commitment as commitment and public_inputs as public_inputs
        
        Note: Hash the input with domain separator
        Let domain_separator_bytes be string_to_bytes with text as FIAT_SHAMIR_DOMAIN_SEPARATOR
        Let hash_input be concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing domain_separator_bytes, challenge_input
        
        Let hash_result be hash.compute_hash with data as hash_input and algorithm as "SHA256"
        Match hash_result:
            When hash.HashFailure:
                Return ZkpFailure with:
                    error as ZkpError.Internal_Error
                    message as "Fiat-Shamir hash computation failed"
            When hash.HashSuccess with value as hash_bytes:
                Note: Convert hash to field element
                Let challenge_result be bytes_to_field_element with bytes as hash_bytes
                Return challenge_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ZkpFailure with:
            error as ZkpError.Internal_Error
            message as "Fiat-Shamir challenge generation error: " plus error as String

Note: Utility Functions

Process called "create_default_setup_parameters" returns ZkSetupParameters:
    Note: Create default setup parameters for ZKP systems
    Let default_params be ZkSetupParameters with:
        proof_system as ZkProofSystem.Bulletproofs
        security_level as DEFAULT_SECURITY_LEVEL
        circuit_size as 1024
        random_oracle as "SHA256"
        curve_parameters as curve.get_standard_curve with name as "P-256"
        field_parameters as field.create_prime_field with prime as "21888242871839275222246405745257275088548364400416034343698204186575808495617"
    
    Return default_params

Process called "hash_circuit" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Compute hash of circuit for identification
    Try:
        Let circuit_serialized be serialize_circuit with circuit as circuit
        Let hash_result be hash.compute_hash with data as circuit_serialized and algorithm as "SHA256"
        Match hash_result:
            When hash.HashSuccess with value as circuit_hash:
                Return circuit_hash
            When hash.HashFailure:
                Return empty list
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "field_elements_equal" that takes a as field.FieldElement and b as field.FieldElement returns Boolean:
    Note: Compare two field elements for equality
    Try:
        Return field.compare with element1 as a and element2 as b is equal to 0
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "serialize_circuit" that takes circuit as ZkCircuit returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Serialize circuit to byte array for hashing
    Try:
        Let serialized be empty list
        
        Note: Serialize circuit size
        Add ((circuit.circuit_size right_shift 24) bitwise_and 255) to serialized
        Add ((circuit.circuit_size right_shift 16) bitwise_and 255) to serialized
        Add ((circuit.circuit_size right_shift 8) bitwise_and 255) to serialized
        Add (circuit.circuit_size bitwise_and 255) to serialized
        
        Note: Serialize gates
        For gate in circuit.gates:
            Add (gate.gate_type as Integer) to serialized
            For input in gate.inputs:
                Add ((input right_shift 8) bitwise_and 255) to serialized
                Add (input bitwise_and 255) to serialized
            Add ((gate.output right_shift 8) bitwise_and 255) to serialized
            Add (gate.output bitwise_and 255) to serialized
        
        Note: Serialize constraints
        For constraint in circuit.constraints:
            Add (constraint.constraint_type as Integer) to serialized
            For variable in constraint.variables:
                Add ((variable right_shift 8) bitwise_and 255) to serialized
                Add (variable bitwise_and 255) to serialized
        
        Return serialized
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "string_to_bytes" that takes text as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert string to UTF-8 byte array
    Let bytes be empty list
    For i from 0 to (length of text minus 1):
        Let char_code be character_code_at with text as text and index as i
        If char_code is less than 128:
            Add char_code to bytes
        Else:
            Add 63 to bytes  Note: '?' for non-ASCII (simplified)
    Return bytes

Process called "concatenate_byte_arrays" that takes arrays as List[List[Integer]] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Concatenate multiple byte arrays
    Let result be empty list
    For array in arrays:
        For byte in array:
            Add byte to result
    Return result

Process called "Clear_toxic_waste" that takes toxic_waste as Dictionary[String, Any] returns None:
    Note: Securely clear toxic waste from memory
    Try:
        Note: Zero out all sensitive values
        For key in keys of toxic_waste:
            If toxic_waste[key] is List[Integer]:
                For i from 0 to (length of toxic_waste[key] minus 1):
                    Set toxic_waste[key] at index i to 0
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Best effort cleanup